How to create new project
Steps:
Go to file
New Project->  make sure it's under Java--> hit next, next---> Put name---> Finish

Make a new Package
Make a new text file
Go to VSC and enable it
it will select Git to be default, if not selet Git.
Red color file means: un-versioned (file not kept track of)
Green file: ready to be part of a repository
You made local repository
Commit and it will open commit window.
Un-versioned Files need to be expanded
Check mark your text files
Make a message in the Amend
Then hit Commit
It will go to local repository
For every new Project go to Git--> GitHub---> Share Project on GitHub
Then you can commit and push as many files as you want

